<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Multiple security issues (cross-site scripting, cross-site request 
forgery, SQL injections, missing input sanitising) have been found in 
Cacti, a web frontend for RRDTool. </p>

<p>For the stable distribution (wheezy), these problems have been fixed in
version 0.8.8a+dfsg-5+deb7u3.</p>

<p>For the testing distribution (jessie), these problems have been fixed in
version 0.8.8b+dfsg-6.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), these problems have been fixed in
version 0.8.8b+dfsg-6.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your cacti packages.</p>
</define-tag>

